genresAdvancedInfo.name: canadian rockabilly
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Canadian rockabilly is a subgenre of rock and roll that originated in Canada in the 1950s. It combines elements of country, blues, and rock and roll, and is characterized by its upbeat tempo and twangy guitar sound. Canadian rockabilly artists often draw inspiration from American rockabilly legends such as Elvis Presley and Carl Perkins.
